column5: Picked up Terry in Orillia, shortly after 7am.. and headed for the lake over yonder to meet up with Lloyd/Keith/Drew and Dale. Was great to be able to get out and grab some fresh air and the resultant head clearing. Keith got a few nice fish.. including a 3 lb pickeral, while Lloyd nabbed an OOS 5 lb laker and a nice big pickeral. Terry and I just washed our lures.. but was a great shake down for me to make sure all the equipment was ready for the season.  mini raviloi for a late breakfast..    6" of ice... up from less than 2 last week!    Getting the water ready for Mr. Noodles lunch.    I don't believe in small baits and finnesse !!! LOL
Excellent that you got out Wayne.  Sorry we missed it, but next time, we'll arrive in style  Well at least you ate well  Joey
LOL I never thought of a fuzzy through the ice.  Nice to see some getting out on the hard water. All my ice plans so far have fallen through I hope to get out before the new year.

that is my kind of ice fishing! When in my boat I go hardcore...no time to eat. But on the ice I'm just like you...crack out some food, share a few laughs etc. for me ice fishing is more of an "experience" than summer fishing.

It was good to get out fishing with you Lloyd and the boys  I didn't take any pictures and I didn't catch any fish  but I did use the underwater camera  I saw 2 walleye and barely got them recorded and ad have some video to show how my camera can be set to auto rotate which makes it easy to find my jigs I cut 3 holes one for the camera and one for each jig, I could see on the monitor better then the recorder recorded it but I will figure it out sooner or later   <object width="480" height="385"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P9pMQePMxco?fs=1&hl=en_US"></param><param'>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P9pMQePMxco?fs=1&hl=en_US"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P9pMQePMxco?fs=1&hl=en_US" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="480" height="385"></embed></object>

Stupid cameras. Same goes with flashers the first time you use one. You see a fish come in and you STOP doing what you were doing to bring the fish in. The fish comes in and takes a look at a bait that's not moving and continues on.  Nice to be able to see them though..
I have to agree. I've never used any kind of electronics ever while ice fishing. And I've never ever been skunked. Sometimes technology goes too far imho.
awesome video terry it's going look cool when you hook one on video
I am so busy watching them I forget to set the hook

Well thats to bad DanC i feel for you. But being the nice guy i am, i will let you come out fishing with me and we will break that trend !  Guaranteed, i have references. GBW, yonge_one,Canadian Copper,Tracker,speckchaser.
Did ya get to test out those new rod holders ya made a few weeks back?
Yes I did Nick... and if I can get a video down and up loaded you can see how nice they work. With the howling wind we had yesterday it even allowed the rod to become an automatic jigger!!!

That was nice to see everyone out Yesterday. Its to bad the fish were not active. That wind was crazy!! At one point I thought I would be sitting in my hut moving 100km the way it was blowing me when I went to the other side of the lake. Terry that video is cool. I have fished that lake 12 years now and never seen the bottom. The two eyes you seen were nice too. I think they seen the sign that I put under your hut that says (MY NAME IS TERRY)so they swam away )lol
Now I could see me doing that too  Maybe I won't try the electronics after all ... or maybe I will....
Good that you got out, Wayne!!  Gotta love that Mini Ravioli, breakfast of champions, lol!  That video, Terry posted is hypnotic.
Would have hated to see your artistic masterpiece ruined by you hooking an actual fish.  Thanks for takin' the time.

Here ya go Nick..  <object width="640" height="385"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vwx_TANloCY?fs=1&hl=en_US"></param><param'>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vwx_TANloCY?fs=1&hl=en_US"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vwx_TANloCY?fs=1&hl=en_US" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="640" height="385"></embed></object>
Great to see you got out for a few hours Wayne. Tough to beat a few hours on the lake to clear the head.
Very cool vid Terry,  Glad to see you out there Wayne.
There ya go eh    Nice subtle action jigging, no hands required.  Would work good on Simcoe, no shortage of wind there.

Awesome Wayne    Glad you got out and get to enjoy a different scenery for a change Testing out the gear, having a late breakfast lunch and sharing the hard surface amongst friends.... PRICELESS Thanks for sharing Leechman

"C and C" catch and consume "C and R" catch and release "W and W" wait and watch  Nice "W and W' report guys...  Wayne -Cool setup ....better get a patent on that Terry- Cool video  but....wayta miss that fish "W,W and W" wait /watch and watch it swim away)
